Titolo: IndyCar Racing

Anno: 1993

Descrizione: IndyCar Racing is a racing video game by Papyrus Design Group released in 1993. Papyrus, consisting of David Kaemmer and Omar Khudari, previously developed Indianapolis 500: The Simulation, released in 1989.
The game was intended as a realistic simulation of IndyCar's 1993 PPG Indy Car World Series. The game featured a selection of the contemporary chassis and engines and eight circuits which could be raced individually or as part of a championship season.  Subsequent expansion packs added a further seven tracks and, later, the Indianapolis Motor Speedway.The game was followed up two years later by a sequel, IndyCar Racing II.

